<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41189f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41189f">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41189f"> 189(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> conjoined</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[<font size="-1">PERSONAL CHARACTERISTICS</font>]</font> The closing scenes of Swedenborg&apos;s life are in keeping with its peaceful tenor throughout. He had no fear of death, but rather joyful anticipation. &ldquo;If,&rdquo; he said to Cuno, &ldquo;any one is <mark>conjoined</mark> with the Lord, he has a foretaste of the eternal life in this world; and if he has this, he no longer cares so much about this transitory life.&rdquo; <small> George Trobridge, <a name="GTLS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#GTLS"><cite title="source">A Life of Emanuel Swedenborg</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (??) 313 [320]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
